Product name: Vintage SIGNED Miriam Haskell Pearl Jewelry Set, Demi Parure, Miriam Haskell Vintage Jewelry, Estate Jewelry, Antique Jewelry Set, C1960s
Description:
This stunning demi parure set was made by jewelry designer, Miriam Haskell, C1960's. 
*Necklace - Condition: Good
The necklace features 12mm blueish-gray faux glass pearls with small glass spacer beads between each pearl. The clasp is a "J" hook adorned with a small blue beaded flower. The necklace is classified as in "good" condition as there is some discoloration in the pearls, and several have some slight peeling, although that is difficult to see. I used a magnifying glass. Also noted, there is one spacer bead missing, but is not overly apparent, see last photo. There is patina commensurate with age and the Miriam Haskell signature mark is noted on the "J" hook. Still a lovely piece in good wearable condition and have priced it accordingly. It measures 15" in length with a 3" beaded extender. 
*Bracelet - Condition: Very Good
The bracelet features a double strand of both 8mm and 10mm blueish-gray faux glass pearls with small glass spacer beads between each pearl. It is finished with a box clasp beautifully detailed with a large gold gilt flower motif featuring a large blueish-gray baroque pearl, violet-blue rhinestones and opaque blue glass beads. The Miriam Haskell signature is noted as the cartouche design. It is classified as in "very good" condition as there is some slight discoloration between each pearl and some very slight patina at the clasp. It measures 7" in length.
*Brooch - Condition: Excellent
The brooch is done in a crescent moon shape beautifully detailed with a stunning 20mm blueish-gray baroque pearl, violet-blue rhinestones and opaque blue glass beads creating a burst of flowers surrounded with gold gilt leaves. It is classified as in "excellent" condition. The c-clasp closure is in working condition and the Miriam Haskell signature is noted on the back in an oval plaque. It measures 2" long by 2" wide at its widest point. It is a show stopper!
*Earrings - Condition: Very Good
The earrings are detailed with a large gold gilt flower motif featuring a large blueish-gray baroque pearl, violet-blue rhinestones and opaque blue glass beads. They are classified as in "very good" condition. The clip tension in both earrings works with no issues. They do have some light patina commensurate with age. The Miriam Haskell signature is noted on the back of both clips. They measure 1 1/8" tall by 1 1/8" wide at the widest point.
Miriam Haskell jewelry is well known for its intricate details and hand wired workmanship and continues to be highly sought after and very collectible. Her jewelry was well known and worn by the women of society of her time and some of her well known customers were Joan Crawford, Lucille Ball and the Dutches of Windsor to name a few. 
Russian gold plating also known as RGP, is a rich looking gold plating that was used extensively by the Miriam Haskell jewelry line. The gold plated dipping solution contained 24-kt gold, among other (secret) ingredients. (Source: Miriam Haskell Jewelry by Cathy Gordon & Sheila Pamfiloff).
*This set has been authenticated through design elements specific and unique to Miriam Haskell jewelry. (Source: Miriam Haskell Jewelry by Cathy Gordon & Sheila Pamfiloff).

Product name: 1940s UNSILVERED PURPLE Stripes Glass Christmas Ornament, Rare Wartime Ornament, Vintage USA Unsilvered Ornaments, Vintage Purple Ornaments
Description:
Wonderful American made unsilvered wartime Christmas ornament In rare pastel colors! Circa 1941-1945.
This is a hard to find vintage USA WWII blown glass ornament featuring a lovely transparent purple glass painted with four colorful stripes. White is the thickest, then turquoise, yellow, and pink. It measures 2 inches wide and retains its original scalloped metal cap which is stamped, "Made in U.S.A." Both the glass and cap are in excellent condition. There are a couple of yellow paint smears, and the cap is oxidized. This vintage glass ornament was made by Corning, one of the early American Christmas ornament manufacturers. 
This is a wonderful 1940s USA unsilvered round striped purple glass Christmas ornament, a great addition to any war era ornament collection.
SIDE NOTE: Metallic mercury glass ornaments get their shine from being coated on their interior with a silver nitrate solution. In 1941, WWII wartime shortages restricted this material, and ornaments during this time frame were produced without silvering. Since unsilvered ornaments were less popular than the shiny mercury glass, they are harder to find and thus more collectible.
See our entire collection of fabulous vintage and antique Christmas ornaments and decorations in our fun Etsy shop, "Just Vintage Christmas":

Product name: Vintage Marc Jacobs Wallet - Red Leather Wallet - Silver Metal Snap Front - Damaged Kiss Lock Does Not Close - Debit Cards - Currency - Chic
Description:
Vintage Marc Jacobs - Red Leather Wallet - Silver Metal Snap Front - Currency Section - Damaged Kiss Lock - Does Not Close - Clean - Chic - Authentic
This is a vintage red leather designer Marc Jacobs authentic wallet.   Clean condition showing signs of wear and use.  The kiss lock clasp is broken.  The change purse portion of this wallet is in disrepair.  Perhaps it could be repaired....but the change purse does not stay closed on its own due to the missing/broken half of the kiss lock closure.  The metal frame is in good condition but the change purse does not stay closed.
I have used a larger sized hair tie to hold the change purse closed and it works well actually....with minimal visibility on the hair tie.  Then the change purse stays closed and can hold coins safely.
Otherwise, in vintage good condition showing signs of age and wear.  No missed stitches or unraveling.  The red leather is clean; it has patina on the outside and shows some ink marks on the inside.  The inside of the change purse is creamy suede.  Beautiful detailing. 
Not too shabby for its vintage age and intended use.  Still has lots of high fashion designer wear left to give.  List price adjusted to account for less than perfect condition.
It weighs 6 ounces prior to packaging for safe transit.  It measures approx. 4" by 4" when clasped and opens to a full 9".  The currency section measures 7-1/4" long. The wallet is approx. 1-1/2" thick.   
The inside has two distinct sections....one for 6 card storage and another two-tiered section for paper currency or receipts.  All sections are nicely lined and appear in clean condition with some ink pen marks here and there....nothing terribly unsightly.
The red leather feels marvelous, the front clasp works as designed and this vintage wallet has a nice weight to it.  
There is a silver metal tab on the inside, etched "Marc Jacobs Made in Italy".  Clean condition; vintage designer goodness.
Suitable for upcycling into a new keepsake.  Suitable for practical use before and after repair to the kiss lock frame.  
Nice little wallet to store cards and paper keepsakes that aren't used on a daily basis.  
Clean and well kept.  Enjoy!

Product name: 1930 Carl Zeiss Jenna Tessar F4.5 15cm View Camera Lena
Description: I am pleased to offer to the Etsy  Community an excellent 1930 Carl Zeiss View Camera Lens. This is a F/4.5 15cc lens that some would consider to be one of the finest Tessar lenses ever made. Tessar formula lenses were invented by Carl Zeiss and provided a remarkable jump in optical quality enabling highly improved available light photography and may be considered similar to the development of coated lenses vs non-coated lens. This lens despite being over 80 years may still be used with a viewfinder camera or any optical device.The lens has a 32mm screw thread. It may be adapted to fit literally any view camera with an inexpensive adapter. Please view the pictures and email me if you have any questions about this remarkable piece of optical glass.

Product name: Vintage Military Shoulder Bag, Army Canvas Messenger Bag, Green Light Canvas Army Bag, Cross Body Bag, Unisex Military Haversack
Description:
Vintage Military Shoulder Bag, Army Canvas Messenger Bag, Green Light Canvas Army Bag, Cross Body Bag, Unisex Military Haversack
***********************************************
This genuine unused military shoulder bag is made from light canvas in army green shade. The shoulder strap is adjustable and wider on the shoulder for comfortable wearing. The bag has two inside compartments, a strap for under flap fastening, with a D-ring attached, wide flap with thick cow leather loops in a nice brown shade. It fastens with two canvas straps with metallic buckle. All loose straps have metallic tips painted in dark military green to match the rest of the shoulder bag. 
If you want a bag with stamps please take a look at this article: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/238182604/vintage-military-shoulder-bag-army?ref=shop_home_listings
 and send me a note to seller on purchase. But please take into consideration that the canvas of these two listings is very different. The one listed here is not so heavy like the one in the other listing of which I have more than just one piece. 
This type of military shoulder bag was typically used in the Communist era by the infantry of the Romanian army. My father still remembers them from the time when he had to do his military duty on the Black Sea Coast. 
This authentic Romanian Army item can be carried cross-body and is ideal for daily use. You can use the bag for your iPad, books, notebooks and other stuff you carry with you every day. The small compartment can hold a compact camera, your phone or even a small bottle. The shoulder bag is very versatile, unisex and just looks fabulous fashionable for its age. The bag is also a perfect gift for him, for the traveler, for the person who loves hiking, camping, and fishing. 
*********************************************
CONDITION: Good vintage condition. This is an unused vintage military bag, it was deposited for long years so there may be a tiny scent that I find negligible and that will go away with time. If you want your bag to smell like new you can wash it when you receive it. Being made of fabric it is really easy to wash, I would recommend you to wash it by hand to preserve the colors better. Some of the metal parts may be bit rusty but this just adds to the vintage character of the item. 
DIMENSIONS: 
Bag: 32 x 32 x 12 cm / 12.5 x 12.5 x 5 inches
Strap: 55 cm / 21.5 inches 
*********************************************
For better viewing of the messenger bag please enlarge the pictures on the zoom button right under the main image. All photos are of the actual vintage messenger bag listed. If you need more pictures please don't hesitate to contact me.

This listing is for one VELOUR beach towel. 
**Understanding Beach Towel Materials**:
Velour towels are softer than terry towels. For Velour towels, the top part of the each loop is shaved allowing a softer feel. Terry towels have hoops on both sides of the towel so it is more abrasive. Again, our towels are velour.
Our beach towels use fiber reactive dyes, They form a covalent bond with the fabric. They become "one" with the fabric. They will not fade in the sunlight or while washing.

--3.LETTERING COLOR.--
Black, rose gold, gold, or silver ink. White ink can be used on dark, solid backgrounds ONLY. It is not as completely opaque as others and tends to look more like chalk. I recommend sticking with black, rose gold, gold, or silver due to this. Watercolor can be used on a white background only (see my Live in the Sunshine canvas for an example of watercolor lettering). 
--4. WRITING STYLE.--
All cursive, or combination of cursive and print (see my listings for examples). I do not recommend all print because all print tends to leave the canvas looking very empty. 
‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ Example ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ 
1. I love you and I like you.

CERTIFIED CRUELTY FREE
FREE COTTON BAG WITH EACH PURCHASE HANDMADE BY WOMEN IN FIJI

Kate and myself are big into sustainability and caring for our planet! The perfumes contain no animal ingredients and we are strongly against products that have been tested on animals.
We do not support the logging of New Zealand native timber, our pots are made from sustainable beech wood. This eco-friendly alternative is sourced from certified sustainable New Zealand forests. A new tree is planted for every one that is logged.

Product name: Natural Remineralizing Toothpaste, 8oz || remineralizing, calcium, magnesium, coral calcium, herbal, natural, coconut oil, xylitol
Description:
Enjoy an unrivaled feeling of clean! You'll have polished teeth, fresh breath, and whiter teeth within the first few uses. Natural minerals and botanical oils scrub away plaque and stains, and anti-bacterial herbs remove built up plaque and biofilm.
User reports: 
A large reduction in plaque and mucous, fresh breath, and translucent tips filling back in. Others also found relief from hot and cold sensitivity that wasn't well controlled with OTC sensitive toothpaste formulas.
Why this formula was created: 
Shortly after birthing my third child, I had pain in almost every tooth. Upon researching tooth pain, I learned that I had experienced a serious demineralization, also known as enamel loss. I had heat and cold sensitivity, pain in several developing cavities, and a cracked molar that went down to the root. I could wiggle each molar half independently of each other, and the exposed nerve made me jump any time food touched it. Chewing on the side of my mouth with the cracked molar was impossible, and enjoying coffee or ice cream was definitely out of the question.
I researched how to fix my problem as I desperately imagined the massive dental bill, and came across mineralizing toothpastes. I was just getting started in the natural healing and herbal world and tried several recipes. Baking soda was really disgusting, clay made me gag. I questioned why I would need baking soda as it is very abrasive (and salty), or clay, which pulls out instead of depositing? Determined, I continued on experimenting and eventually wound up with this wonderful recipe.
My results: Sensitivity and pain, gone. Healthier teeth. Whiter teeth. Cleaner teeth. Fresh breath.
Contains NO: parabens, sulfates, flouride, salts, clays, nor baking soda. It will not clog your drains as some clays can.
Ingredients: Coral calcium, calcium magnesium carbonate, diatomaceous earth, xylitol, coconut oil, olive oil, distilled water, burdock root, oregon grape root, plantain leaf/stem, echinacea extract,  xantham gum, potassium sorbate,{lemon essential oil, orange essential oil, rosemary essential oil, red thyme essential oil for Lemon Thyme flavor} OR {peppermint essential oil, sage essential oil for Sage Peppermint flavor}
Suggested Use: Squeeze a pea sized amount onto toothbrush, scrub teeth, gums, and tongue. Rinsing is optional, it is completely safe to swallow - great for children and people with special needs who can't spit well.

Product name: Around the Sun and Seasons Work--Montessori Celebration of Life--Montessori Birthday Celebration
Description:
Living in Arizona, we do not get to experience the change of seasons, it is summer pretty much year round. So I love anything that helps my children visualize how beautiful seasons are!
 This set does it all! It includes a felt mat with removable seasonal trees and the sun, labels for months and seasons as well as 3 laminated cards on colored cardstock per season. Colors of details on felt seasonal trees may vary from photos above depending on availability.
 It can be used for traditional Montessori birthday celebrations with a candle placed in the center of the sun. The birthday child is invited to stand in front of the month they were born in holding a globe (optional) and to walk around the sun back to their month symbolizing the number of years they've lived. Lovely way to incorporate science in a birthday celebration. Doubles as seasons work with sorting activity.
Cards are cut prior to laminating and then cut again after to insure complete seal around each piece, corners are rounded for safety. They are classroom sturdy, completely waterproof, will not split or peel.

Product name: Blue Music Box, Small Music Box, Manual Music Box, Disney Frozen Music Box, Acrylic Music Box, Children's music box, Custom music box.
Description:
This manual hand crank music box brings back all the nostalgia of childhood. Slowly turn the handle to hear and 18 note melody. A piece of fossil glass has been attached with a plant preserved right inside the glass. Choose from one of 12 available tunes, listed below.
What a perfect gift for that little girl in your life, or even for yourself. What makes this collectible music box even more special is the fossil glass jewelry on the top, transparent just like the music box. The deep aqua colour is especially beautiful.
Spend time listening to the sound of the notes the music box plays and re-live the happy memories from your childhood.
Song choices:
Disney Frozen Let it Go
Somewhere Over the Rainbow
You are my Sunshine
Love Story
Happy Birthday
Edelweiss
Twinkle Little Star
Canon in D
Fur Elise
La vie en Rose
Amazing Grace
Lullaby
** Indicate your song choice in a message to seller when you check out.
Size and attachment: 
The music box is made from acrylic and has a mechanical crank that plays 18 notes when slowly turned. 
The music box portion measures 8cm x 5cm x 3cm. The inside mechanisms are made of metal. 
The fossil glass portion measures 1.75 inches x 1.5 inches and is 1/4 inch thickness.
What is this fossil glass attachment?
The piece of deep aqua botanical fossil glass contains a plant that has been turned to carbon between layers of glass. A tiny piece of nature preserved forever! Eco friendly! Also a nice gift for the plant lover or scientist! I make all the fossil glass in my small home studio, and the plants I use are taken from my own property without harming the larger plant. 
The plant is burned away in a special oven at almost 1500 degrees! What you see is the ash remains, sealed within the glass as it melts around the plant.
Thank you for stopping by my shop!

Description:
3D Printed Miniature Zelda Themed Nintendo Entertainment System Case for Raspberry Pi 2 Model B and Pi 3 with Green LED.
Made from tough, Eco-Friendly PLA material. The micro SD card slot features a Hylian Shield engrave so you can remove the micro sd card much easier without having to take the case apart. Also included is an LED cutout and pre-wired (with resistor) Green LED already glued into place. I will include an easy wiring diagram for hooking the wires up to the proper GPIO pins, very simple and just slips on. The led will turn on when the power is on and off when power is off, just like a real Nintendo. Everything is 3D printed. The Wingcrest lid is 100% 3D printed and not a cheap sticker or decal. Even the LED lense insert that diffuses the LED light is 3D printed.
You will not find another NES case like this on Etsy, it is truly one of a kind.

Description:
Vintage silver plate fork set, hand stamped with saying of your choice. Please keep in mind the stamping space on a fork is limited so if you are concerned about saying length please contact me before ordering.
HOW TO ORDER:
1. Select quantity from the drop down menus on the listing.
2. If the option is available, choose whether you want the date or name(s) stamped on the handle or not from the drop down menu. (If you do leave the date in mm.dd.yyyy or mm.dd.yy format or name(s) in notes to TheRusticStamp section at checkout)
3. Add to cart.
4. If you have a custom request or favorite silver style? Feel free to let me know in the notes to TheRusticStamp section at checkout. 
5. Checkout (Please make sure your shipping address is correct, this can be changed when I go to create a shipping label but when I am busy I make no guarantees that I will remember to do that)
*Please remember all my products are silver-plated vintage silverware, this means they are not brand new. There may be some minor signs of wear from their previous lives (this includes minor scratches, minor plate loss or minor pitting) although I do my best to find silverware without wear. Also please expect for there to be a flat spot on the backside of the spoon behind each letter from the hammering process. 
**Also please note all my items are made to order. So no two items will be exactly alike and you will not receive the exact product in the picture. I personally stamp each letter/design by hand so please allow for slight variations in placement, spacing and straightness, all of this just adds to the handmade charm of the product. 
***For all of my items I go through the process of hand picking the silverware, hand polishing, hand stamping, hand washing for use and then packaging. All items are food safe, some people choose to use them on a daily basis and others choose to use it for display. I do recommend hand washing items and hand drying them. This helps reduce tarnishing (as a lot of dishwashing detergents contain bleach) as well as water spots. As vintage silver plated items naturally tarnish over time I do recommend using a silver polishing cloth to remove tarnish.

Description:
Save by buying by twos -- get two skeins for 20!! That's 5 off of two skeins -- a 20% savings! Hurry and get yours -- supplies are limited.
When silk fabric is cut and made into saris, wraps, and veils, there is always a bit left over. Rather than throw that waste fabric into the trash, it has been made into a beautiful, unique, soft yarn! Direct from India, this yarn is a truly recycled product! It is a bulky weight and is soft and easy to knit or crochet. 
These skeins are slightly bigger than some others that are listed on Etsy and come in gorgeous, saturated colors -- purples, blues, greens, golds, yellows, pinks, silvers and more! They are very soft and light! Each skein / hank weighs approximately 3.5 ounces (100 grams) and measures 50-60 yards of ribbon. The width of the yarn varies from 1/2-inch to 1-1/2 inches and each section of color is about 1 yard in length; all sections are sewn together end to end to make these continuous multicolor masterpieces!
Upon purchase, you will receive two multicolor skeins. Though no two skeins of this ribbon are exactly alike, they are all very similar and contain the same color groups. All are of similar color shades and can be considered complimentary and coordinating.
This yarn makes wonderful hats, scarves, bags, trim, fringe, wraps, jewelry and more!
Get creative with silk this season and save!

Product name: Niddy Noddy - 1 yard Collapsible Travel Size Bamboo
Description:
This handy little niddy noddy tool is used to wind the yarn you've spun into a skein off of your drop spindle or spinning wheel bobbin.  Its press fit construction holds it securely together while in use, yet it easily collapses flat into two pieces for easy storage.  It is easily taken apart and reassembled.  The diameter of your skein will be 1 yard which also makes it useful for skeining smaller amounts of spinning.  Its short length allows it to fit easily into your spinning bag, making this the ideal travel tool for any spinner.  No more trying to jam a standard 2 yard niddy noddy in only to have it hang out the top!  
This affordable niddy noddy is laser cut from durable bamboo plywood.  Each piece is hand sanded after laser cutting to smooth out corners and edges to make sure that your yarn slides smoothly off of each end. It measures approximately 4.5"x10" when assembled and 5"x7"x1/4" when collapsed and inserted into its packaging.  Your niddy noddy will arrive to you in a padded envelope in a reusable sheath made of elastic straps mounted onto thick cardboard.  You may want to continue storing it in this packaging to keep both pieces together to ensure its longevity.   
It is important to me that each item I make is special and bamboo contributes to this as a unique material. Bamboo plywood is sustainable and is stronger than wood. Your niddy noddy tool won't be indestructible but can withstand a lot of yarn winding. Bamboo has a rich history of roles and uses in Asian mythology and culture and is even used in Chinese medicine because of its anti-bacterial properties. 
To assemble, hold a piece of the niddy noddy in each hand and match up the slots.  The two ends will be perpendicular to each other with the long part of each piece forming the center shaft as they come together.  To use your niddy noddy you'll be holding it at the center of the shaft.   Start by wrapping the loose end of the yarn around the top left end a couple times, trapping your initial wrap underneath your working yarn to secure it.  From the top left you'll cross down and under the right handle, then back up and over the left end of the top handle, then back down under the right end of the lower handle.  Once you're out of yarn, weave the loose ends of your skein through to secure them and prevent tangling.  Then slip the yarn off the ends of the niddy noddy handles.  To twist the yarn into a skein, slip the fingers of each hand through either end of the skein and twist in opposite directions until the yarn twists back onto itself.  Tuck one end into the other and you have a twisted skein.  
Because it is made of a natural material, the appearance of each piece may slightly vary. Please contact me if you would like a custom tool based on this design.  If you would like me to etch a name or (short) message onto it, please leave it in the notes when you check out.

Product name: Polymer Clay Tutorial ENGLISH ONLY Pdf Format - Masterful Faux Made Easy
Description:
This tutorial is offered in English only.
Polymer Clay PDF Tutorial Diva Designs Masterful Faux Made Easy 
In this tutorial, I will teach you my technique for creating realistic-looking turquoise similar to Carico Lake Turquoise, Fox Turquoise, African or Yellow Turquoise, Chinese Turquoise, Number 8 Turquoise, King Manassa Turquoise, Kingman Turquoise, Pilot Mountain Turquoise, Purple Turquoise, Boulder Turquoise, Royston Turquoise, White Buffalo Turquoise, and my versions of Dalmation Jasper, Orange Sponge Coral, Sonora Sunrise, African Jasper, Blue Lapis and Pink Rhodochrosite.
My favorite gemstone is turquoise.  It amazes me that you can find so many hues of blues and greens in one stone, so naturally, it was the first stone I tried to recreate when I started working with polymer clay six years ago.  I had some good results, but was never completely satisfied because I could not accurately capture the natural matrix in genuine turquoise.     
The key to a realistic-looking faux polymer turquoise is duplicating a great matrix, those crackled lines and mottled, speckled spots which appear in genuine turquoise.  Turquoise matrix can be black, brown, golden brown, red, and even turquoise in color.  It can be very pronounced in some stones, and hardly visible to the eye at all in others; such as the rare and extremely expensive Sleeping Beauty Turquoise, which is almost entirely a bright sky blue.  
Turquoise is also one of the most duplicated faux finishes in polymer clay.  There are many recipes and tutorials out there for polymer turquoise.   My method is fun, easy to do, and does not require expensive tools and equipment.  
This technique does not require a high level of skill to successfully create the faux finishes included.  If you can condition clay and possess the basic tools, materials and supplies every polymer artist uses on a daily basis, you will be able to use this tutorial with ease.   If you are new to polymer clay and do not have these every day items, email me and I will help you with a list of the basic items you will need in addition to the materials and tools list included for this specific tutorial, none of which are expensive or difficult to find. 
As with my Controlled Marbling Tutorial, this tutorial is intended to be about the technique.  I include suggestions on how to use recipes, with photos and some basic instructions for earrings, a slide, a pendant and coin beads.  The suggestions are intended to be guides and are not specifically "projects."   They do not include finishing tips or instructions.  
Please note that alcohol inks are used in some of the recipes included in the tutorial.  As much as possible, I have tried to include substitutes to be used instead of alcohol ink for those of you who may not be able to find every color of Ranger and/or Pinata Alcohol Ink on the market, particularly those of you who live outside the U.S.   If I have not included a substitute, email me and I will do my best to help determine a good substitute for you.  
If you live outside the U.S., postal regulations prohibit delivery of items containing alcohol from being mailed through the post office.  It is my understanding they must be mailed via ground delivery, meaning UPS or FEDEX. 
The tutorial also contains numerous tips from me which I have learned through trial and error and happily pass along to you, which I hope will help make the creative process easier, more fun, and more successful for you. 
My goal in writing my tutorials is to make you feel as if I am sitting right beside you as you create.  I research my techniques for months before I begin to write each new tutorial.  If you have any questions about the process or need clarification about any part of the tutorial, I am always available to help if you need assistance. 
Some basic knowledge and experience with polymer clay is helpful, but not absolutely necessary. The instructions are aimed at the novice and the experienced clayer. 
Trish Hodgens at www.polyclayplay.com has generously agreed to offer my customers a discount off the supplies in my tutorials that she carries.  Trish will carry as many of the supplies and materials as possible used in my tutorials. Each tutorial has its own discount code, and I will email it to you upon purchase.  If you don't hear from me within 24 hours, please contact me here through Etsy.    
NOTICE: You may sell work you create using this tutorial, but any redistribution, re-sale or reproduction of the tutorial itself, in whole or in part, in ANY form, is strictly prohibited. If I determine that you are redistributing or selling any part of my tutorials, you will be barred from purchasing from my shop and I will take whatever legal action available to me to prosecute the theft of my property. To be clear, this means you may not share any part of this tutorial with a friend or family member who has not paid me for that additional copy or material first. If you want to order a copy for someone else, I would be happy to deliver it to an email address of your choosing as a gift from you. You may not share a print-out of, or your actual digital copy of, this tutorial in a polymer clay class, or guild meeting, either in person or digitally via Skype or other internet outlets or social media websites. I regret that I even have to mention this, but unfortunately, it has become necessary to address this issue. 
Thank you! 
Lynda

Product name: Crushed Pyrite or Fool's Gold, Medium, 1 Ounce
Description:
This mineral's metallic luster and pale brass-yellow hue give it a superficial resemblance to gold, hence the well-known nickname of fool's gold. I have seen this mineral crushed and used in jewelry and it looks amazing! This material is perfect for small voids or small accents, with unlimited applications. Each of our products are handpicked to ensure superior quality (removal of host rock or other naturally occurring minerals).
Material Size and Quality:
Medium - material is considered to be medium to fine (sand), ranging between 2 millimeters to 0.25 millimeters (between sieves #10 - #60).
This product is NOT man-made, mixed with resin, or stabilized. Please be careful when buying crushed mineral since most products have a caveat in fine writing that states that this stone might be man-made, mixed with resin, or is made from a composite (generally, plain stone mixed with a dyed resin to make the product seem authentic and is allowed to be called natural). Stone authenticity is extremely important to all artisans; therefore, we strive to validate the source of all our minerals before they are processed and sieved.
As with any naturally occurring minerals, there can be some matrix or host rock mixed in with the product. However, we hand pick each unit to ensure that our product is of the highest quality. Please see product images for color, size, and quality. Picture taken in full - material is dry.

Multi use powder brush (2) 
Use these brushes to remove excess powder and give the finishing touch for a professional look. 
Face brush (3) 
These face brushes are ideal for loose or compact powder, bronzers and blush application. The soft bristles easily pick up the right amount of powder.
Foundation brush (1) 
Use these brushes for liquid foundation and concealers. Its firm bristles soak up less of the liquid makeup and you have the perfect coverage for a natural look. 
Eye shadow brush (10)

Lip brush (3)

Sponge eye shadow brush (1) 
Sponge eye shadow brush creates smooth blending of colours for a professional look. 
Eyebrow/eyelash comb, brush
Stainless steel slant tip eyebrow tweezers
We recommend washing the brushes before first use in warm soapy water, rinse well under warm running water, reshape and allow to air dry for 24 hours.

Description:
An easy-to-follow sewing pattern (downloadable PDF) for making a bunny or bear soft toy - designed by Margeaux Davis from Willowynn.
This vintage-style bunny doll or bear soft toy is the perfect companion for a little person. Designed to be endlessly carried around and looks so sweet nestled in amongst a child's pillows. - Dark embroidery floss to stitch eyes and nose.
- Templates (included in PDF pattern) cut out.
- Hand sewing needles ‚Äì one for embroidery thread and another for finer thread.
- Fabric marker or ball point pen
- Fabric scissors
- Pins
- Long surgical tweezers or a haemostat (for stuffing).

‚ùñ IMPORTANT NOTE ‚ùñ
Each piece of personalized jewelry is caringly hand stamped by me, one at a time, never stamped by a machine.  I use the hand stamped technique to create your unique, one of a kind, piece of jewelry; no two will be exactly the same.  Please know I try very hard to make each and every piece beautiful during the stamping process but there may be some curvature or slight imperfections on the disc and in letter placement and spacing, this is what makes your piece of jewelry so special.  Also note that the disc is only stamped on the front and the back of the disc will have a slight imprint of the letter from stamping imprint of the letter. ‚ùñ CLEANING AND CARING FOR YOUR JEWELRY ‚ùñ
To ensure that your jewelry stays bright, keep it in an airtight container or a sealed bag like Ziplock. After each use quickly give it a clean with a dry cloth before placing into airtight bag or container. We recommend putting your jewelry on last when getting ready, as direct exposure to hair-styling products and perfume will often also damage the metal and gemstones. Do NOT use jewelry when swimming in chlorinated, thermal or salt water OR when showering. Also avoid wearing silver while exercising as this will cause sweat and other toxins, which can contribute to tarnish.
To clean, use a non-abrasive cleaning material like a mild dish washing liquid diluted in water. Use a polishing cloth to restore the shine after washing. Paste or strong jeweler cleaner is not recommended for plated metal as it may remove the plated silver or gold. Do not let your jewelry come into contact with nail polish removers, perfume or hairspray.

****** IMPORTANT STUFF ABOUT SIZING & COPPER RINGS ****** 
Since the band is wider than a standard ring, I recommend going up a half size bigger than your usual thin band size. If you size your ring for a wider band of at least 3/16ths inch, use that size.
Many people find that wearing jewelry containing copper or brass will cause a darkening (green) on the skin where the metal touches. This discoloration comes off with soap and water and is not harmful.  If you are not wearing the ring for health benefits, you may want to apply a thin layer of clear nail polish to eliminate the discoloration. Since people often wear copper jewelry to help with issues such as arthritis, I do not apply sealants to the metal.
Like the rings but you have something *slightly* different in mind? Send me a message through Etsy to discuss it :)

This is a very sophisticated process and only a few mills in the world do it. You should not mistake this process for gold plating as there is a very big difference.

Embroidering will be done on umbrellas with a 42" arc. It has the auto-open feature!  They are all Totes brand, so you know you are purchasing a quality umbrella!  It will last for years to come!
When ordering, please include the full name of the recipient and I will put the initials in the correct order according to which monogram style you choose from the drop down menu.  Please note in the monogram style picture above, the left hand side has monograms with first, LAST, middle initial, and the right hand side has monograms with first, middle, last initials.
In the notes to seller, (copy and paste this part to make it easier)
1. Full name of recipient (first, middle, and last)  
2. Color of thread
3. Monogram style (see last picture)
4. Double check the spelling, color thread, and monogram style!
